LAGOS  – Bola Tinubu Support Organisa­tion in the United Kingdom and Diaspora (BTSOUK), organised a South West Nigeria stakehold­ers meeting on Saturday 19, 2022 in Lagos to mobilise political leaders in the country towards supporting the presidential bid of Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu. The meeting converged lead­ers of the group from the three senatorial areas of the state, in­ cluding local government coordi­nators from the 57 LGA’ and Lo­cal council areas to brainstorm on mobilisation strategies ahead of their planned mega rally. Prince Tunde Edward, whois the coordinator of the group in Lagos, said the group was solely established to mobilisehuge sup­port for Asiwaju in the coming presidential election in 2023. He said, “Our primary objec­tive is to ensure that the large number of Tinubu supporters is indeed registered with their PVC’s in readiness for the election. “To achieve this, we lined up anumberof strategicprojectsto encourage the voting public and to give them an understanding of the blessings that will accrue from the Tinubu presidency. Our mobilisation efforts will culminate into the hosting of a Mega Rally in Lagos between the months of April and May this year.” He added. Prince Olusanya, the group’s leading patron said, “Owing to the highly successful tenure of Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu as a Governor in Lagos State, we are convinced about his ca­pabilities to successfullyrule this country. “The roll call of outstanding leaders Asiwaju has produced right from the Vice president to others, including notable infrastructural projects that has turned Lagos into a smart city and the high level of security found in the state, were achieved because of the solid foundation he laid for successive governors of the state.” Stressing that the achievements and many more, he said he has convinced members of the group beyond any doubt that Asiwaju is indeed the best material for the presidency at the moment.